    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-06-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-06-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="754"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d754">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2001.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Mexican Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-06-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 8, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 54.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Referring to your note of the 19th ultimo,
                    communicating to the Department a request of your Government that measures be
                    taken to prevent the enlistment of men in the United States for the invasion of
                    Lower California, I have the honor to inform you that I am advised by the
                    Attorney General, under date of the 30th ultimo, that this matter is already in
                    the hands of the United States attorney at José Angeles, to whom he has
                    forwarded a copy of your note, with instructions to proceed appropriately in the
                    premises.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
